\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. tunbrigense} (L.) Sm. in Sowerby,{\i  Engl. Bot. }{\b 3}: t. 162 (1794). Lamina usually 22-45 × c. 15 mm, flat, somewhat glossy, slightly bluish-green. Indusium-valves suborbicular, fimbriate-dentate in the distal 1/2 nearly flat. 2n = 26. {\i Woods and other damp, shady, sheltered places. Locally in W.. Europe from N. Spain to Scotland; Açores; a few isolated stations eastwards to N. Italy.} Az Be Br †Cz Ga Ge Hb Hs It †Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. H. wilsonii} Hooker, {\i Brit. Fl.} 450 (1830) ({\i H. unilaterale} auct., vix Bory). Like {\b 1} but with usually narrower leaves, which are deflexed laterally and therefore appear even narrower, darker, somewhat olive-green; indusium-valves ovate, entire, convex. 2n = 36. {\i Similar situations to} {\b 1}{\i  but more tolerant of exposure. N.W. Europe; Açores.} Az Br Fa Ga Hb No.
\par

